    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-12-31T16:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1952-01-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="13" subtype="editorial-note"
                type="document" xml:id="d13">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>
                    <persName corresp="#p_UJE1">John E. Utter</persName>, Director of the Office of
                    African Affairs, carried out a trip to more than 20 Foreign Service posts in
                    Africa and 4 metropolitan capitals in Europe during the period May 21 to August
                    1, <pb facs="0085" n="41" xml:id="pg_41"/> 1953. <persName corresp="#p_UJE1"
                        >Utter</persName>’s intent was to consult with principal officers, members
                    of their staffs, and key government officials regarding the general situation in
                    each area visited. No comprehensive record or report of the <persName
                        corresp="#p_UJE1">Utter</persName> trip has been found. A few documents on
                    the arrangements for the trip and summary accounts of visits in Addis Ababa,
                    Benghazi, and Casablanca are included in file 110.22 <gloss target="#t_AF1"
                        >AF</gloss>. A few additional papers on the arrangements for the trip also
                    are included in <gloss target="#t_AF1">AF</gloss> files, lot 58 D 459,
                    “Correspondence 1953”.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
